A recent survey in urban Shanghai revealed high obesity rates among adults and children, mirroring developed countries.
Improved living standards contribute to the rising obesity trend in China, especially among city dwellers.
Lack of exercise, excessive sleep, and high-fat diets are major factors.
The Health Department aims to reduce obesity by 2005, emphasizing lifestyle changes over bans on unhealthy products.
Similar concerns exist in Guangzhou, where poor nutrition affects teenagers' growth and health.
In Kuwait, hypnotherapy shows promise in treating obesity, while in the UAE, diabetes rates are escalating due to obesity.
Education and healthy eating habits are crucial in combating these health issues.
